OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Raymond Briggs used his skills as an   
OL,6, illustrator to articulate his own      
OL,7, acerbic views on people, politics and  
OL,8, society.                               
OL,10,FHis children's books often failed to   
OL,11,Ffollow the established format. His     
OL,12,Fsnowman melted and his Father Christmas
OL,13,Fwas far removed from the jovial figure 
OL,14,Fwe all expect.                         
OL,16,FAn astute observer of the human        
OL,17,Fcondition, his adult work reflected his
OL,18,Fown concerns, such as When the Wind    
OL,19,FBlows, a fable about a nuclear attack  
OL,20,Fon the UK.                             
